.TH "codec_init" 9 "codec_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
codec_init \- Initialize a Reed-Solomon codec
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct rs_codec *" codec_init
.BI "(int symsize "  ","
.BI "int gfpoly "  ","
.BI "int (*gffunc)(int) "  ","
.BI "int fcr "  ","
.BI "int prim "  ","
.BI "int nroots "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "symsize" 12
symbol size, bits (1-8)
.IP "gfpoly" 12
Field generator polynomial coefficients
.IP "gffunc" 12
Field generator function
.IP "fcr" 12
first root of RS code generator polynomial, index form
.IP "prim" 12
primitive element to generate polynomial roots
.IP "nroots" 12
RS code generator polynomial degree (number of roots)
.IP "gfp" 12
GFP_ flags for allocations
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate a codec structure and the polynom arrays for faster
en/decoding. Fill the arrays according to the given parameters.
